This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as open relation extraction. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of neural network-based models, which are commonly used in the field of computational linguistics. 

It could also belong to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve the performance of open relation extraction. 

"cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a hybrid neural sequence tagging model to capture contextual and temporal information. 

"cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as open relation extraction is a task that is closely related to information retrieval. 

Finally, "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks to improve the performance of open relation extraction.
